data.description:
Beneath the Boulder Flatirons and Chautauqua Park, this exquisite residence enjoys stunning mountain views from its tree lined street. Meticulously renovated, this home has been updated with modern convenience and impeccable style. The abundance of natural light flooding the rooms through large windows blends the outdoor and indoor spaces. Come explore the home’s NEW kitchen, NEW hardwood floors, NEW furnace, almost New central air conditioning system, NEW Washer & Dryer, NEWLY re-plastered walls, NEWLY refurbished windows, and NEWLY refinished walkout basement. 

Whether you're relaxing by the fireplace in the front living area, preparing a meal in the open gourmet kitchen, or dining al fresco on the elevated back deck, you'll find that this home offers an unlimited opportunity to live the Colorado lifestyle. The evening mountain sunsets and breathtaking beauty surround you. Offering easy access to walking/ hiking/ biking in Chautauqua Park and the surrounding trails, you simply step out your front door. The Hill, the University of Colorado, and CU football games in Folsom Stadium are only a short walk away. This special home's proximity to Pearl Street with its vibrant shops and renowned restaurants is another fabulous feature. Whether you're looking to explore the great outdoors, visit cultural attractions, or simply enjoy the local community and University, this home's superb location and exquisite renovation offers you an unbeatable Colorado lifestyle. 

** Includes architectural plans for second story addition with garage. 
***Fun fact, this home was originally owned by the mother in law of Frederick Gorham Folsom, the father of CU Football! Historic background in supplements.
****Price is as-is.
